node.text:
This week on Think Loud Crew, the girls talk all about SEX! They go deep about how they lost their virginities, masturbation, their "exploring phase", how sex was like before they had kids, compared to how sex is now after having kids!

Follow us: 
Think Loud Crew IG: @thinkloudcrew
Cheyenne's IG: @cheynotshy
Shanan's IG: @hairbyshananc
R's IG: @rkylelynn

More about the show: 

Check out our YouTube channel to watch the full episode: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCEWHZqlWjGI1ZD9TwHBT8jg.

Don’t forget to subscribe to the podcast for free wherever you're listening or using this link: http://bit.ly/ThinkLoudCrewPodcast

node.text:
Zach asked me if I need all this stuff that I packed in my hospital bag, and I said "Yup, I sure do!." I been through this one time before, and one thing I know is I wanna be in my own stuff at the hospital so I'm comfortable!

Cheyenne, R, and Shanan are back again, and this time they've invited their favorite Teen Mom OG producer, JC Cueva, to talk about his experience of being a traveling producer while still being a full time dad. He gives tips and tricks on how to spend quality time with his kids, even if it's virtually, and talks about what he's learned while being a producer at Teen Mom OG!

Follow JC on IG: @j.c.cueva

node.text:
In this exciting new episode of Think Loud Crew, Cheyenne isn't pregnant anymore!! Ace finally came into this world, and Chey tells all about her 2nd experience giving birth: from her pre-labor contractions, to finally pulling the baby straight out of her!

Birthing a child isn't glamorous, especially if your future father-in-law is present during the birth. Stay tuned to hear all about it!

node.text:
This week on Think Loud Crew, the girls get real about what it’s like to date with children! They talk about their own awkward dating experiences, learning to set boundaries with the people they are dating, dating while also co-parenting, being open with your children, and never settling.

It’s hard being a mom in the dating world, and the girls can relate!

Follow us: 
Think Loud Crew IG: @thinkloudcrew
Cheyenne's IG: @cheynotshy
Shanan's IG: @hairbyshananc
R's IG: @rkylelynn

More about the show: 
Check out our YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCEWHZqlWjGI1ZD9TwHBT8jg.

node.text:
Welcome to our premiere episode of On the Road to Ace with the CRAZ Family!  By the time this series airs, Ace will already be with us, but I wanted to capture the moments in the final weeks of my pregnancy to save forever.  I want to share them with Ace when he gets older, but until then, I want to also share them with you!

I hope you enjoy watching these as much as my family enjoyed making them!

Follow us:
Cheyenne's IG: @cheynotshy
Zach's IG: @z.terrel
Ryder's IG: @thatsryderk

R's IG: @rkylelynn
Baaz's IG: @unbothered_baaz

node.title: On the Road to Ace:  Season Preview

node.text:
This week in Think loud Crew, Cheyenne, R, and Shanan are talking all about social media! How it’s changed, how you use it, how to handle negativity, and their highs and lows while using it. Also, Cheyenne goes deep on what it's like to be a social media influencer!

Not everything is what it seems on social media, and our girls are willing to uncover those truths!

Follow us: 
Think Loud Crew IG: @thinkloudcrew
Cheyenne's IG: @cheynotshy
Shanan's IG: @hairbyshananc
R's IG: @rkylelynn

More about the show: 
Check out our YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCEWHZqlWjGI1ZD9TwHBT8jg.

Don’t forget to subscribe to the podcast for free wherever you're listening or using this link: http://bit.ly/ThinkLoudCrewPodcast

node.title: The Social Media Experience: Highs, Lows, & Everything in Between

node.text:
This week on the Think Loud Crew Podcast I talk about my labor & delivery with Ace. Everything from pre-labor contractions, to finally pulling Ace straight out of me! Child birth is the craziest yet most beautiful experience you can go through. Hope you tune into our podcast to hear my story and subscribe to our YouTube channel! 🖤✨ 
@thinkloudcrew

node.text:
Ryder absolutely loves her new #BittyBaby from @americangirlbrand  #ad  
Baby Marshmallow arrived around the same time as Ace, and we are a full house right now with Ryder helping nurture both babies! Thank you, American Girl, for contributing to Ryder’s new mommy experience. We love seeing her learn how to feed and change diapers to become an even greater big sister to Ace! The Bitty Baby line is available on AmericanGirl.com & AG stores. Use code CHEYENNE15 for 15% off one order online through 8/1. Exclusions apply.
